1
00:00:00,660 --> 00:00:02,045
Hi. I'm Billy.

2
00:00:02,070 --> 00:00:03,095
Billy Dooley.

3
00:00:03,120 --> 00:00:04,865
That's me. I'm asleep.

4
00:00:04,890 --> 00:00:07,490
I hate to start this whole thing
off in a state of unconsciousness

5
00:00:07,515 --> 00:00:09,907
but I was having this weird
dream about my relatives.

6
00:00:09,932 --> 00:00:11,544
For some reason we were all on the beach

7
00:00:11,569 --> 00:00:12,935
playing volleyball.

8
00:00:12,960 --> 00:00:16,115
Look Joe, our grandson Billy Dooley.

9
00:00:16,140 --> 00:00:19,393
Come here and give your
grandma a great big kiss.

10
00:00:19,617 --> 00:00:20,858
No, grandma is OK.

11
00:00:23,046 --> 00:00:24,995
Throw yourself into the game boy.

12
00:00:25,020 --> 00:00:28,930
You're not gonna embarrass yourself
in front of people like you did last year.

13
00:00:28,955 --> 00:00:31,296
No, I promise grandpa.
It won't happen again.

14
00:00:31,321 --> 00:00:34,330
Of course not, not with moves like yours.

15
00:00:36,660 --> 00:00:38,400
Sorry, hurt your Billy?

16
00:00:38,425 --> 00:00:39,758
Only when I breathe.

17
00:00:40,545 --> 00:00:42,498
No, cousins.

18
00:00:42,900 --> 00:00:46,020
Don't worry.
It's okay for second cousins to kiss.

19
00:00:46,045 --> 00:00:48,206
I want my piggy back ride.

20
00:00:48,231 --> 00:00:49,624
Wanna lick my Popsicle?

21
00:00:49,649 --> 00:00:50,649
No, thank you.

22
00:00:50,674 --> 00:00:52,954
Pimples. I gotta kiss those pimples.

23
00:00:52,979 --> 00:00:54,814
- Hello Billy
- Meema.

24
00:00:55,225 --> 00:00:56,630
Mom, dad. This is hell.

25
00:00:56,655 --> 00:00:58,895
Honey, they're just happy to see you.

26
00:00:58,920 --> 00:01:00,151
They sure are, son.

27
00:01:01,380 --> 00:01:02,495
That's right.

28
00:01:02,520 --> 00:01:05,273
- And you know who's dying to see you?
- Who aunt Margaret?

29
00:01:05,298 --> 00:01:06,950
Your cousin Mark.

30
00:01:07,384 --> 00:01:09,631
Come here Billy, see.

31
00:01:09,944 --> 00:01:11,950
No, not Mark Jr.

32
00:01:24,847 --> 00:01:26,186
Hurt your Billy?

33
00:01:33,976 --> 00:01:35,582
I'm gonna get you Billy.

34
00:01:40,650 --> 00:01:42,060
You have our attention now Billy.

35
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:44,200
What is it?

36
00:01:45,270 --> 00:01:46,884
Nothing, I'm fine.

37
00:01:47,103 --> 00:01:48,510
You think that dream was insane?

38
00:01:49,050 --> 00:01:51,451
You should see some of the
others I've been having this week.

39
00:01:51,660 --> 00:01:54,390
If you ever been to a family reunion,
I'm sure you can relate.

40
00:01:54,540 --> 00:01:57,240
My family, the Dooley’s, have
these dreaded events every year.

41
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:58,890
By now, you'd think we'd know better.

42
00:02:03,033 --> 00:02:05,553
He's even more uptight
about this thing than you are.

43
00:02:05,790 --> 00:02:08,023
Grace. I'm not uptight.

44
00:02:08,048 --> 00:02:09,048
Really?

45
00:02:09,073 --> 00:02:11,440
Why are you driving on
the wrong side of the road?

46
00:02:16,141 --> 00:02:18,090
This is good. This is really good.

47
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:20,838
We've been on the road two hours yet

48
00:02:20,863 --> 00:02:22,033
it feels like two weeks.

49
00:02:22,950 --> 00:02:26,530
Mom, a suggestion. We could turn
back the clock, turn around and go home.

50
00:02:27,448 --> 00:02:29,200
- Got my vote.
- I'm there.

51
00:02:29,490 --> 00:02:30,490
Kevin.

52
00:02:30,641 --> 00:02:33,990
It is your grandmother's 100th birthday,
we told everyone we're going.

53
00:02:34,740 --> 00:02:35,740
We're committed.

54
00:02:36,180 --> 00:02:39,000
Believe me, after a weekend
with my family we will be.

55
00:02:44,233 --> 00:02:46,420
Dad, I told Keith I would call him.

56
00:02:46,733 --> 00:02:48,519
Yeah, but every ten minutes?

57
00:02:48,546 --> 00:02:49,586
Dad, come on.

58
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:52,110
I told you a hundred times.

59
00:02:52,402 --> 00:02:53,666
If you're gonna talk to Keith.

60
00:02:53,691 --> 00:02:56,424
You get a job. You get a car.
You get a car phone.

61
00:02:56,449 --> 00:02:58,615
- Why are you yelling at her?
- I'm not yelling at her.

62
00:02:58,640 --> 00:03:01,209
- Now you're yelling at me.
- Because you're yelling at me.

63
00:03:01,234 --> 00:03:02,514
You know why everyone's yelling?

64
00:03:02,539 --> 00:03:06,169
Because we're driving to the murky
depths from which there is no return.

65
00:03:06,717 --> 00:03:10,410
They made disguises in this reunion but
all these people want do is compete,

66
00:03:10,435 --> 00:03:14,035
show each other up and put each other down.
Why are we putting ourselves through this?

67
00:03:16,526 --> 00:03:17,526
Because

68
00:03:19,503 --> 00:03:20,503
we are family.

69
00:03:20,528 --> 00:03:23,941
If someone would have given me a
choice between parting with my relatives

70
00:03:23,966 --> 00:03:26,610
or spending the weekend
in a maggot infested barrel.

71
00:03:27,108 --> 00:03:28,740
The maggots would have won hands down.

72
00:03:29,970 --> 00:03:31,590
Some of you may think I'm overreacting

73
00:03:32,640 --> 00:03:33,640
just wait.

74
00:03:39,210 --> 00:03:41,691
Isn't that the exact same
position we left them in last year?

75
00:03:41,716 --> 00:03:45,310
The only thing that's changed is they
filed down the horns of Mark Jr.'s head.

76
00:03:45,335 --> 00:03:48,555
How much time do you think I'd get about
knocked them over like bowling pins.

77
00:03:49,473 --> 00:03:51,599
A lot if I testify against you.

78
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:53,200
Say hello.

79
00:03:54,060 --> 00:03:55,060
Hello sister.

80
00:03:55,410 --> 00:03:56,640
OK, here's how it works.

81
00:03:57,210 --> 00:04:00,010
I cannot stand my cousin Mark Jr.

82
00:04:00,035 --> 00:04:02,203
My dad is not too fond of Mark senior,

83
00:04:02,228 --> 00:04:04,410
my mom is not exactly
thrilled with aunt Margaret.

84
00:04:04,889 --> 00:04:05,889
My sister

85
00:04:06,476 --> 00:04:07,680
she hates them all.

86
00:04:07,705 --> 00:04:08,705
Well

87
00:04:08,730 --> 00:04:11,370
if it isn't my brother
and his lovely family.

88
00:04:11,640 --> 00:04:12,681
I didn't think you'd show.

89
00:04:13,290 --> 00:04:14,730
Why would you think that sister?

90
00:04:15,210 --> 00:04:16,710
Shall I list the reasons?

91
00:04:16,735 --> 00:04:17,735
No, don't.

92
00:04:17,760 --> 00:04:19,903
We're just here to have
a good time this year.

93
00:04:20,640 --> 00:04:22,656
I'm glad you're here

94
00:04:22,681 --> 00:04:24,330
makes things a little
more competitive.

95
00:04:25,080 --> 00:04:26,080
Very little.

96
00:04:26,250 --> 00:04:27,250
So, moron.

97
00:04:27,450 --> 00:04:29,450
Are you gonna humiliate
yourself again this year?

98
00:04:29,970 --> 00:04:30,970
Stuff it Mark.

99
00:04:31,710 --> 00:04:32,710
Clever.

100
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:35,853
With that steel trap of a mind of yours
that I heard get you thrown back

101
00:04:35,878 --> 00:04:37,029
into summer school.

102
00:04:42,615 --> 00:04:43,962
- Smooth move.
- Thank you.

103
00:04:44,700 --> 00:04:45,831
Race you to the front door.

104
00:04:46,411 --> 00:04:47,814
My brother hasn't got a chance.

105
00:04:49,980 --> 00:04:51,011
Kevin don't do it.

106
00:04:51,784 --> 00:04:53,265
I can beat him, he's on a bike.

107
00:04:53,290 --> 00:04:54,570
That's not the point.

108
00:04:55,063 --> 00:04:56,063
Yes, it is.

109
00:05:02,374 --> 00:05:03,374
He's cheating.

110
00:05:04,212 --> 00:05:05,759
And this surprises you?

111
00:05:15,438 --> 00:05:16,673
I can't believe it.

112
00:05:25,998 --> 00:05:27,600
Pretty good driving there, pal.

113
00:05:27,625 --> 00:05:30,624
I hope you're not too tired
later for a round of golf.

114
00:05:31,534 --> 00:05:32,534
See you.

115
00:05:34,078 --> 00:05:35,195
Don't worry dad.

116
00:05:35,220 --> 00:05:37,780
Maybe he'll get a massive
coronary like on Ethel's first husband.

117
00:05:37,940 --> 00:05:40,325
That's not a very nice thing to say.

118
00:05:40,350 --> 00:05:42,150
No, but it's optimistic.

119
00:05:43,231 --> 00:05:44,231
Alright.

120
00:05:44,850 --> 00:05:45,850
Let's get this over with.

121
00:05:47,220 --> 00:05:48,220
Let's go.

122
00:05:50,593 --> 00:05:52,473
Jeez, did I hurt you?

123
00:05:53,132 --> 00:05:54,132
No.

124
00:05:54,157 --> 00:05:56,953
No, that's all right.
It happens all the time.

125
00:05:58,010 --> 00:05:59,440
Welcome to Jameson Bluffs.

126
00:05:59,465 --> 00:06:01,505
I'm Donald Jameson, your concierge.

127
00:06:01,890 --> 00:06:03,630
I'll get the boy to help
you with your bags.

128
00:06:04,806 --> 00:06:05,806
Douglas!

129
00:06:08,946 --> 00:06:11,286
Hello, I'm bellhop Douglas.

130
00:06:12,180 --> 00:06:13,373
Welcome to Jameson Bluffs.

131
00:06:13,590 --> 00:06:15,580
How may I help you take your bags?

132
00:06:16,516 --> 00:06:18,000
How how did you do that?

133
00:06:19,080 --> 00:06:20,080
Do what?

134
00:06:23,159 --> 00:06:24,159
Never mind.

135
00:06:32,256 --> 00:06:33,729
It's a nice place in here.

136
00:06:35,580 --> 00:06:37,590
Welcome to the Jameson Bluffs.

137
00:06:37,860 --> 00:06:39,806
A family run resort.

138
00:06:41,326 --> 00:06:44,092
I think family run is
the operative word here.

139
00:06:44,117 --> 00:06:45,117
Yes.

140
00:06:45,540 --> 00:06:47,999
Mom, don't you think
that's a little creepy?

141
00:06:48,706 --> 00:06:49,815
You want creepy?

142
00:06:49,840 --> 00:06:50,840
Turn around.

143
00:06:52,178 --> 00:06:54,138
Boo-Boo. Cuddles.

144
00:06:54,753 --> 00:06:58,406
Aunt Kate,
don't call us that we're not kids anymore

145
00:06:58,431 --> 00:07:02,340
To me you'll always be Boo-Boo and Cuddles.

146
00:07:03,570 --> 00:07:05,069
Isn't that right?

147
00:07:07,260 --> 00:07:08,403
You're right aunt Kate.

148
00:07:13,649 --> 00:07:14,649
Cute?

149
00:07:14,674 --> 00:07:15,756
So cute.

150
00:07:16,362 --> 00:07:20,430
Billy, I'm so glad you're here.
Your cousins have been dying to see you.

151
00:07:20,610 --> 00:07:22,260
Every family has a few

152
00:07:22,470 --> 00:07:23,470
losers cousins.

153
00:07:23,850 --> 00:07:26,250
Unfortunately, all of
mine fit that description

154
00:07:26,460 --> 00:07:27,460
Billy.

155
00:07:27,510 --> 00:07:28,530
Want a piece of gum?

156
00:07:29,829 --> 00:07:30,936
What are you worried about?

157
00:07:30,961 --> 00:07:31,961
I don't got cooties.

158
00:07:34,287 --> 00:07:37,322
I want a piggyback ride right now.

159
00:07:37,347 --> 00:07:39,000
Later, later.

160
00:07:40,975 --> 00:07:41,975
Look.

161
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:45,748
I get the complete mint stamp
collection of the Elvis commemorative.

162
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:48,270
Greg still doesn't talk

163
00:07:48,390 --> 00:07:49,650
just like aunt Seal.

164
00:07:49,770 --> 00:07:52,543
She didn't say giddily squad
until her first communion

165
00:07:52,568 --> 00:07:53,928
and then you couldn't shut her up.

166
00:07:54,663 --> 00:07:56,376
Yada yadada. Right?

167
00:07:56,760 --> 00:07:58,290
Yada yadada Greg.

168
00:07:58,470 --> 00:07:59,999
Can you say yada yadada?

169
00:08:03,156 --> 00:08:04,156
William.

170
00:08:05,370 --> 00:08:06,370
Hello William.

171
00:08:06,656 --> 00:08:08,529
Amber, it's good to see you again.

172
00:08:08,940 --> 00:08:10,048
I've grown up William.

173
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:11,800
Can't you tell?

174
00:08:13,530 --> 00:08:14,890
I can actually.

175
00:08:15,210 --> 00:08:16,680
My dad needs help with the bags.

176
00:08:16,883 --> 00:08:18,456
But I need help too.

177
00:08:18,900 --> 00:08:20,009
Smell me William.

178
00:08:20,610 --> 00:08:21,690
It's obsession.

179
00:08:22,899 --> 00:08:23,899
It certainly is.

180
00:08:23,924 --> 00:08:26,872
I know you've been
uncomfortable in the past

181
00:08:27,365 --> 00:08:28,715
but great news.

182
00:08:28,740 --> 00:08:30,060
I've done all the research.

183
00:08:30,570 --> 00:08:33,240
Second cousins can propagate.

184
00:08:36,090 --> 00:08:37,356
Amber, you're very weird.

185
00:08:37,860 --> 00:08:38,860
I can't help it.

186
00:08:39,540 --> 00:08:41,190
You bring out my dark side.

187
00:08:45,153 --> 00:08:48,180
Through your left you will notice
the children's recreation area.

188
00:08:48,780 --> 00:08:51,510
And to you're right you
will notice a fully equipped

189
00:08:51,780 --> 00:08:52,780
heated pool

190
00:08:53,040 --> 00:08:54,040
loaded with water.

191
00:08:59,446 --> 00:09:00,446
They're your parents.

192
00:09:01,079 --> 00:09:02,860
They're your parents. There's your father.

193
00:09:02,885 --> 00:09:04,485
- Say hello.
- Do I have to?

194
00:09:05,195 --> 00:09:06,997
You better think of something,
here they come.

195
00:09:07,082 --> 00:09:08,729
Douglas, could you stop the car please?

196
00:09:09,930 --> 00:09:10,930
Thanks.

197
00:09:13,780 --> 00:09:15,600
Great darling.

198
00:09:15,746 --> 00:09:16,746
Daddy.

199
00:09:17,573 --> 00:09:20,285
Kevin, give your mom a big kiss.

200
00:09:23,185 --> 00:09:27,390
And look at that boy and
how much he's grown.

201
00:09:28,243 --> 00:09:30,810
Connie, you are so beautiful.

202
00:09:30,930 --> 00:09:32,760
I love you both.

203
00:09:36,390 --> 00:09:39,000
Well, come on you too say hello.

204
00:09:42,261 --> 00:09:44,280
They hadn't spoken in a long time

205
00:09:44,550 --> 00:09:47,527
so getting them to say hello is like
getting rid of a pimple on prom night.

206
00:09:48,283 --> 00:09:49,283
Hello.

207
00:09:50,845 --> 00:09:51,845
Hello.

208
00:09:51,870 --> 00:09:54,039
See. That wasn't so hard, was it?

209
00:09:54,064 --> 00:09:55,290
As a matter of fact it was.

210
00:09:56,092 --> 00:09:57,374
Now that I think about it.

211
00:09:57,399 --> 00:09:58,772
I take the hello back.

212
00:10:01,950 --> 00:10:05,518
You know your father,
he doesn't mean anything he says.

213
00:10:05,543 --> 00:10:06,720
Yeah, except in my case.

214
00:10:10,334 --> 00:10:11,334
So.

215
00:10:11,804 --> 00:10:12,944
Where's the guest of honor?

216
00:10:13,301 --> 00:10:16,581
Meema, she's lying down
for her afternoon nap.

217
00:10:30,614 --> 00:10:31,655
Are you sure she's asleep?

218
00:10:31,934 --> 00:10:34,514
You never can be sure with that one.

219
00:10:35,324 --> 00:10:36,850
But I did lock her in.

220
00:10:37,419 --> 00:10:38,419
Yeah.

221
00:10:38,444 --> 00:10:40,084
What did I do with that key?

222
00:10:44,058 --> 00:10:45,610
I think I've lost it.

223
00:10:47,618 --> 00:10:49,134
Here we go.

224
00:10:49,827 --> 00:10:51,973
This will be your home for a while.

225
00:10:52,304 --> 00:10:54,434
I hope you enjoy your lagoon view.

226
00:10:55,484 --> 00:10:57,344
And your television set.

227
00:10:57,690 --> 00:10:59,569
It will be cable compatible

228
00:10:59,594 --> 00:11:02,893
with 105 channels except for
some reason it doesn't get channel 2.

229
00:11:02,894 --> 00:11:04,700
I don't know why.
Crazy day.

230
00:11:04,964 --> 00:11:07,664
But I certainly hope you enjoy
your commendations here

231
00:11:07,977 --> 00:11:09,679
at the fabulous Jameson Bluffs.

232
00:11:09,704 --> 00:11:10,704
Thank you.

233
00:11:13,550 --> 00:11:14,550
Welcome.

234
00:11:15,154 --> 00:11:18,647
I just put some fresh
towels in your bathroom.

235
00:11:18,884 --> 00:11:20,414
If there's anything you need

236
00:11:20,439 --> 00:11:21,439
I'm Donna

237
00:11:21,464 --> 00:11:23,625
and if there's anything you
don't need I'm still Donna.

238
00:11:27,403 --> 00:11:29,643
Thank God we're not
at their family reunion.

239
00:11:31,156 --> 00:11:35,675
How clever, Margaret and Mark
have made up a whole itinerary.

240
00:11:35,700 --> 00:11:36,700
Golf.

241
00:11:36,725 --> 00:11:37,725
Tennis.

242
00:11:37,750 --> 00:11:39,670
Volleyball. 500 meter swim?

243
00:11:40,424 --> 00:11:42,224
Only thing they left out is the luge.

244
00:11:42,584 --> 00:11:44,654
Wrong honey, look,
page three you missed it.

245
00:11:45,104 --> 00:11:46,424
10:30 Sunday.

246
00:11:46,741 --> 00:11:49,157
My back is hurting just thinking about it.

247
00:11:49,874 --> 00:11:51,224
I'm gonna need a chiropractor.

248
00:11:51,854 --> 00:11:53,504
Connie, get off the phone.

249
00:11:55,484 --> 00:11:56,484
He's not home.

250
00:11:57,044 --> 00:11:58,844
Where else would he
be on a Friday afternoon?

251
00:11:59,069 --> 00:12:00,524
He'll probably went to the movies

252
00:12:00,974 --> 00:12:02,594
with Mary Ellen Jenkins.

253
00:12:16,137 --> 00:12:17,628
The first time I saw her

254
00:12:17,653 --> 00:12:18,653
it was like

255
00:12:18,678 --> 00:12:19,733
a fantasy

256
00:12:20,577 --> 00:12:22,184
a mist filled vision.

257
00:12:24,528 --> 00:12:26,237
The real fun begins

258
00:12:26,262 --> 00:12:27,654
in 20 minutes

259
00:12:27,679 --> 00:12:29,598
at the family reception.

260
00:12:30,923 --> 00:12:32,384
In an instant the vision was gone

261
00:12:32,409 --> 00:12:33,409
and so was the mist.

262
00:12:35,595 --> 00:12:37,549
Just put a bullet in me now.

263
00:12:38,384 --> 00:12:39,661
It's your family.

264
00:12:43,397 --> 00:12:44,634
The Dooley's.

265
00:12:44,804 --> 00:12:47,053
A proud and prosperous clan.

266
00:12:47,625 --> 00:12:50,294
Who over the centuries
fell into two categories.

267
00:12:50,864 --> 00:12:51,864
Crooks

268
00:12:52,004 --> 00:12:53,084
and lawyers

269
00:12:53,264 --> 00:12:55,334
and the occasional
