Don't worry. Look.

1078
00:55:54,184 --> 00:55:55,204
The best thing you can do

1079
00:55:55,294 --> 00:55:57,544
is just get some sleep, relax

1080
00:55:57,904 --> 00:55:59,224
and let the professionals

1081
00:55:59,674 --> 00:56:00,674
do our thing.

1082
00:56:14,799 --> 00:56:15,799
Where are you going?

1083
00:56:15,824 --> 00:56:18,204
I'm certainly not going to
wait for lieutenant dumbo here.

1084
00:56:18,229 --> 00:56:19,617
I'm looking for Meema myself.

1085
00:56:19,721 --> 00:56:20,721
Where?

1086
00:56:20,746 --> 00:56:21,746
Everywhere.

1087
00:56:23,248 --> 00:56:25,248
If anything happens to Meema.

1088
00:56:25,974 --> 00:56:27,268
I'll never forgive you.

1089
00:56:27,664 --> 00:56:28,664
Me?

1090
00:56:28,807 --> 00:56:30,613
You wanted to get rid
of her as much as I did.

1091
00:56:30,638 --> 00:56:33,000
I wanted her to move in with Kevin.

1092
00:56:33,025 --> 00:56:36,454
I didn't want her to become an
episode of Unsolved Mysteries.

1093
00:56:38,344 --> 00:56:40,484
Are you going to stand there?
Or are you coming?

1094
00:56:40,509 --> 00:56:41,509
I'm coming.

1095
00:56:44,730 --> 00:56:45,838
You heard your mother.

1096
00:56:50,430 --> 00:56:52,772
- Wait. What's going on?
- I can't talk.

1097
00:56:52,797 --> 00:56:54,230
- Move it Mark.
- Get out of here.

1098
00:56:58,381 --> 00:57:00,524
That was the best night of my life

1099
00:57:01,310 --> 00:57:02,900
and the dawn

1100
00:57:03,041 --> 00:57:04,041
those colors.

1101
00:57:05,104 --> 00:57:06,984
I could stay up here forever.

1102
00:57:07,490 --> 00:57:08,717
Yeah, me too.

1103
00:57:09,549 --> 00:57:11,389
But, don't you think we
should be getting back?

1104
00:57:11,413 --> 00:57:12,513
Back to what?

1105
00:57:12,942 --> 00:57:14,930
A bunch of loudmouth blowhards

1106
00:57:14,955 --> 00:57:16,804
who only think about themselves.

1107
00:57:17,137 --> 00:57:18,772
This is what it's all about.

1108
00:57:18,797 --> 00:57:21,604
Flying high free as a pelican.

1109
00:57:22,322 --> 00:57:24,903
Well, even pelicans have to eat.

1110
00:57:24,928 --> 00:57:26,199
I'm starving.

1111
00:57:26,308 --> 00:57:28,034
Well, why didn't you say so?

1112
00:57:28,444 --> 00:57:30,483
Breakfast is being served.

1113
00:57:31,710 --> 00:57:33,349
How do you like your chocolate?

1114
00:57:33,374 --> 00:57:34,789
Light or dark?

1115
00:57:36,214 --> 00:57:37,214
Yes.

1116
00:57:37,301 --> 00:57:38,301
Thank you.

1117
00:57:44,670 --> 00:57:47,014
Good news people, we know where they are.

1118
00:57:47,481 --> 00:57:48,481
Spit it out.

1119
00:57:48,700 --> 00:57:51,250
They're a couple of
thousand feet up in the air.

1120
00:57:51,480 --> 00:57:53,100
Wait, what are you talking about?

1121
00:57:53,524 --> 00:57:55,608
Well, according to our cabana boy.

1122
00:57:55,633 --> 00:57:56,633
Raoul.

1123
00:57:59,929 --> 00:58:01,298
A hot air balloon

1124
00:58:01,323 --> 00:58:06,334
was hijacked yesterday by a woman answering
to the description of your grandmother.

1125
00:58:06,994 --> 00:58:08,434
Who later abducted

1126
00:58:08,627 --> 00:58:12,514
a teenage boy on the 14th Fairway,
isn't that right Raoul?

1127
00:58:14,407 --> 00:58:15,407
Well.

1128
00:58:15,432 --> 00:58:16,472
At least they're together.

1129
00:58:16,559 --> 00:58:17,559
Yeah, that's true.

1130
00:58:17,584 --> 00:58:20,404
I don't know whether
that's a blessing or a curse.

1131
00:58:20,551 --> 00:58:21,940
Well, which way were they going?

1132
00:58:21,965 --> 00:58:23,311
Due west.

1133
00:58:27,125 --> 00:58:29,638
I'm gonna wait here in
case they come back here.

1134
00:58:29,663 --> 00:58:30,743
Don't worry, I'll find her.

1135
00:58:30,768 --> 00:58:32,141
- Be careful.
- OK.

1136
00:58:32,688 --> 00:58:34,508
Kevin. Kevin.

1137
00:58:34,533 --> 00:58:36,194
You got room for another passenger?

1138
00:58:36,219 --> 00:58:38,254
- Sure mom, come on.
- Not me.

1139
00:58:39,956 --> 00:58:40,956
Him.

1140
00:58:41,725 --> 00:58:45,034
I don't want to hear a word, I mean it.

1141
00:58:45,530 --> 00:58:47,523
Now, you get in there.

1142
00:59:06,068 --> 00:59:08,074
How did you get him to do that?

1143
00:59:08,434 --> 00:59:10,444
My usual threat.

1144
00:59:10,894 --> 00:59:11,894
Which is?

1145
00:59:12,034 --> 00:59:13,767
He does what I tell him

1146
00:59:13,792 --> 00:59:16,978
or I stopped programming the VCR for him.

1147
00:59:28,941 --> 00:59:29,941
Bernice.

1148
00:59:30,636 --> 00:59:32,389
Why don't you come with me honey?

1149
00:59:32,414 --> 00:59:34,476
- I could sure use the help.
- I'd love to.

1150
00:59:34,501 --> 00:59:35,624
Come on, hop in.

1151
00:59:37,094 --> 00:59:38,234
Seat belt on.

1152
00:59:51,124 --> 00:59:52,924
Was that a breakfast or what?

1153
00:59:53,884 --> 00:59:55,819
Definitely the breakfast of champions.

1154
00:59:56,464 --> 00:59:57,754
When I was a kid

1155
00:59:58,517 --> 01:00:00,990
I used to eat by weight in candy.

1156
01:00:01,984 --> 01:00:04,354
In fact I ate my weight in everything.

1157
01:00:04,701 --> 01:00:07,207
The word junk food
hadn't been invented yet.

1158
01:00:07,414 --> 01:00:08,684
A good thing too.

1159
01:00:09,214 --> 01:00:10,714
Because that's all I ever ate.

1160
01:00:11,824 --> 01:00:12,824
Between you and me.

1161
01:00:13,204 --> 01:00:16,864
I raid Margaret freezer every
night just to get out the ice cream

1162
01:00:17,854 --> 01:00:20,587
and everybody always blames Mark Jr.

1163
01:00:22,320 --> 01:00:23,854
Why don't you just tell him it's you?

1164
01:00:24,315 --> 01:00:25,315
Why?

1165
01:00:25,340 --> 01:00:27,553
I like to see that kid squirm.

1166
01:00:28,000 --> 01:00:30,574
And then everybody
gets into a big argument.

1167
01:00:33,650 --> 01:00:35,624
You enjoy watching them fight?

1168
01:00:35,957 --> 01:00:38,950
Well, if they didn't fight
they'd never talk to each other.

1169
01:00:39,263 --> 01:00:41,696
I'm just helping them communicate.

1170
01:00:41,786 --> 01:00:42,786
You see Billy

1171
01:00:42,811 --> 01:00:44,371
all those people down there

1172
01:00:44,611 --> 01:00:45,720
every one of them

1173
01:00:45,745 --> 01:00:47,994
has problems with their families

1174
01:00:48,019 --> 01:00:50,215
that drives them up the wall

1175
01:00:50,725 --> 01:00:52,745
and it all gets so important,

1176
01:00:52,770 --> 01:00:54,785
they forget what really is.

1177
01:00:55,402 --> 01:00:58,130
So that's why you have to
eat all the ice cream you can

1178
01:00:58,155 --> 01:01:00,141
while you can still
sink your teeth into it.

1179
01:01:00,166 --> 01:01:02,835
I think you're trying to tell me
something, aren't you Meema?

1180
01:01:03,214 --> 01:01:04,214
No.

1181
01:01:04,414 --> 01:01:06,700
If I wanted to say something direct.

1182
01:01:06,725 --> 01:01:08,762
I'd say talk to your father.

1183
01:01:09,425 --> 01:01:11,872
Like your father should talk to his father

1184
01:01:11,897 --> 01:01:13,865
and his father should talk to me.

1185
01:01:14,372 --> 01:01:18,270
But if I talk direct to anybody,
do you think they'd listen to me?

1186
01:01:18,295 --> 01:01:19,295
No.

1187
01:01:20,072 --> 01:01:22,472
It's a lot more fun just
stealing their ice cream.

1188
01:01:23,852 --> 01:01:25,392
Say. Look at that.

1189
01:01:26,619 --> 01:01:28,292
Everybody's naked.

1190
01:01:28,317 --> 01:01:29,703
It's a nudist colony.

1191
01:01:30,452 --> 01:01:31,452
Let's buzz them.

1192
01:01:36,662 --> 01:01:37,662
Take a right up there.

1193
01:01:40,791 --> 01:01:41,791
Why?

1194
01:01:41,816 --> 01:01:43,152
We don't know where we're going.

1195
01:01:43,789 --> 01:01:45,789
My instinct says take a right.

1196
01:01:46,658 --> 01:01:48,528
Yeah, but your instinct could be wrong.

1197
01:01:48,553 --> 01:01:49,658
But it could be right.

1198
01:01:50,178 --> 01:01:51,992
Why are you so afraid of making a mistake?

1199
01:01:52,468 --> 01:01:54,557
You just want to go in
the direction you're going in

1200
01:01:54,582 --> 01:01:56,321
because that's the
direction you're going in.

1201
01:01:57,216 --> 01:02:00,151
No dad, I'm not afraid
to go in another direction.

1202
01:02:00,176 --> 01:02:02,622
Right and take half my clients with you.

1203
01:02:02,647 --> 01:02:05,107
Look, when I left the
practice I didn't take anybody.

1204
01:02:05,653 --> 01:02:08,762
They chose to come with me,
you were the one who was afraid to change.

1205
01:02:08,999 --> 01:02:10,707
All right, so I'm not afraid anymore.

1206
01:02:10,732 --> 01:02:11,732
Okay?

1207
01:02:13,987 --> 01:02:14,987
Wait a minute.

1208
01:02:15,862 --> 01:02:17,488
Are you admitting you were wrong?

1209
01:02:18,962 --> 01:02:20,268
Will you make a right?

1210
01:02:20,406 --> 01:02:21,406
Please.

1211
01:02:32,580 --> 01:02:33,886
Look, it's her.

1212
01:02:34,299 --> 01:02:35,439
Where is she going?

1213
01:02:35,464 --> 01:02:36,825
What am I? A mind reader?

1214
01:02:36,850 --> 01:02:37,850
Follow her.

1215
01:02:43,830 --> 01:02:45,702
Aunt Kate,
do you mind if I change the radio?

1216
01:02:46,236 --> 01:02:47,356
Go ahead dear.

1217
01:02:49,937 --> 01:02:50,937
I love rap.

1218
01:02:51,196 --> 01:02:52,332
You're kidding, right?

1219
01:02:52,383 --> 01:02:55,670
Well, not at all.
I like the beat and the social commentary.

1220
01:02:56,283 --> 01:02:57,283
You know aunt Kate.

1221
01:02:57,308 --> 01:02:58,308
You're really cool.

1222
01:02:58,333 --> 01:02:59,333
No.

1223
01:02:59,358 --> 01:03:00,358
I'm fresh.

1224
01:03:00,746 --> 01:03:03,692
If you're gonna walk the
walk you got to talk the talk.

1225
01:03:04,868 --> 01:03:06,368
Are you down with that?

1226
01:03:06,393 --> 01:03:07,393
You bet.

1227
01:03:13,566 --> 01:03:14,566
What is it?

1228
01:03:15,362 --> 01:03:16,376
Nothing.

1229
01:03:16,401 --> 01:03:17,967
Aunt Kate, do you think I could drive?

1230
01:03:17,992 --> 01:03:20,914
You know, I have my learner's permit
but my mom never has time to take me.

1231
01:03:21,184 --> 01:03:22,184
I don't see why not.

1232
01:03:22,411 --> 01:03:23,411
Thanks.

1233
01:03:25,131 --> 01:03:26,417
She's pulling over.

1234
01:03:26,792 --> 01:03:27,792
I can see that.

1235
01:03:30,436 --> 01:03:33,221
- What is she doing?
- What does it look like they're doing?

1236
01:03:33,246 --> 01:03:35,286
Well, it looks like she's
going to go out and drive

1237
01:03:35,311 --> 01:03:37,197
and then the older
woman is going to get into...

1238
01:03:37,537 --> 01:03:38,737
Follow her.

1239
01:03:39,212 --> 01:03:40,562
Okay. Okay.

1240
01:03:45,642 --> 01:03:47,962
Teacher, this is driver's education.

1241
01:03:51,708 --> 01:03:52,708
Look.

1242
01:03:52,733 --> 01:03:54,068
Everyone's going the other way.

1243
01:04:04,232 --> 01:04:05,719
What do we do now?

1244
01:04:06,525 --> 01:04:08,672
What do I look like? The auto club?

1245
01:04:09,002 --> 01:04:10,231
Get out of the car.

1246
01:04:12,047 --> 01:04:13,047
No.

1247
01:04:17,009 --> 01:04:18,009
Witch.

1248
01:04:20,252 --> 01:04:21,252
Not bad?

1249
01:04:22,655 --> 01:04:23,962
Not bad at all.

1250
01:04:24,135 --> 01:04:25,641
I wouldn't get so excited.

1251
01:04:25,768 --> 01:04:28,988
Another few years and
gravity will attack them too.

1252
01:04:29,417 --> 01:04:32,444
It'll take a forklift to keep their
butts from hitting the ground.

1253
01:04:32,469 --> 01:04:34,795
Meema, speaking of gravity
I think we got a problem here.

1254
01:04:35,665 --> 01:04:36,762
We're out of gas.

1255
01:04:36,851 --> 01:04:38,497
- Look, there they are.
- Where?

1256
01:04:38,522 --> 01:04:39,522
Over there.

1257
01:04:39,547 --> 01:04:40,547
Look.

1258
01:05:00,610 --> 01:05:01,610
Sam, we got a break-in.

1259
01:05:01,842 --> 01:05:03,242
People wearing clothes.

1260
01:05:03,267 --> 01:05:05,223
That's right, I repeat,
people wearing clothes.

1261
01:05:09,382 --> 01:05:12,661
Nothing brings a family closer
together than a stint in the big house.

1262
01:05:12,686 --> 01:05:13,686
In fact,

1263
01:05:13,711 --> 01:05:17,161
this is the most time any of us had
spent together in one place in years.

1264
01:05:19,796 --> 01:05:22,076
Let us out of here, you dirty rats.

1265
01:05:23,123 --> 01:05:25,349
I've always wanted to be able to say that.

1266
01:05:25,501 --> 01:05:28,154
I'm thrilled that somebody's
having a good time.

1267
01:05:30,415 --> 01:05:31,828
A nudist colony.

1268
01:05:32,288 --> 01:05:33,834
I've never seen so many...

1269
01:05:34,334 --> 01:05:35,334
Neither have I.

1270
01:05:35,466 --> 01:05:36,912
Well, I hope not young lady.

1271
01:05:37,644 --> 01:05:39,185
What's the matter with you?

1272
01:05:39,632 --> 01:05:42,919
Bodies are beautiful no
matter what shape they're in.

1273
01:05:43,652 --> 01:05:45,665
Considering the last time I worked out was

1274
01:05:45,690 --> 01:05:47,690
1952

1275
01:05:47,715 --> 01:05:49,116
I have to say that.

1276
01:05:52,802 --> 01:05:56,372
How about some grub back here,
this place isn't fit for dogs.

1277
01:05:57,175 --> 01:05:58,175
Jeez lady.

1278
01:05:58,200 --> 01:05:59,455
Put a lid on it.

1279
01:06:00,002 --> 01:06:01,661
We didn't get any sleep last night.

1280
01:06:01,795 --> 01:06:05,492
You shouldn't be sleeping,
you should be working on a jailbreak plan.

1281
01:06:06,101 --> 01:06:08,781
I want to hear shovels digging a tunnel.

1282
01:06:09,055 --> 01:06:10,055
Let's go.

1283
01:06:10,587 --> 01:06:13,321
Maybe someone give
us a cake with a file in it.

1284
01:06:13,652 --> 01:06:14,940
You think this is funny?

1285
01:06:15,785 --> 01:06:17,358
I want to go to law school, pal.

1286
01:06:17,931 --> 01:06:19,665
This might go on my permanent record.

1287
01:06:20,758 --> 01:06:24,669
How depressed will I be when the
world is deprived of one less slimy lawyer.

1288
01:06:24,851 --> 01:06:28,262
Wise guy, this whole thing is your fault.

1289
01:06:28,442 --> 01:06:29,552
- His fault?
- Yeah.

1290
01:06:29,628 --> 01:06:32,556
- How is it his fault?
- Because he encouraged her.

1291
01:06:32,581 --> 01:06:35,627
He went along for the ride instead
of trying to talk some sense into her.

1292
01:06:35,652 --> 01:06:37,754
Have you tried talking sense to Meema?

1293
01:06:37,779 --> 01:06:39,587
Don't mouth off to me.

1294
01:06:39,612 --> 01:06:40,662
That's right.

1295
01:06:40,687 --> 01:06:42,778
Who said sense is such a good thing?

1296
01:06:42,803 --> 01:06:44,723
Well, he just should
have stopped it, that's all.

1297
01:06:44,748 --> 01:06:47,289
Look dad, things happen all right.

1298
01:06:47,612 --> 01:06:49,622
Somebody isn't always to blame.

1299
01:06:50,192 --> 01:06:52,682
He try so hard to control everybody.

1300
01:06:53,012 --> 01:06:55,272
Instead of just seeing who they are

1301
01:06:55,498 --> 01:06:57,482
and just loving them for it.

1302
01:06:57,784 --> 01:06:59,478
Look, don't lecture me, all right?

1303
01:06:59,690 --> 01:07:01,784
Well, somebody's gotta talk to you.

1304
01:07:04,262 --> 01:07:06,872
Just because people don't
do what you want them to do.

1305
01:07:07,448 --> 01:07:08,868
Doesn't mean they're wrong.

1306
01:07:09,888 --> 01:07:11,004
It just means they're...

1307
01:07:11,861 --> 01:07:12,861
people.

1308
01:07:25,745 --> 01:07:26,745
Thanks dad.

1309
01:07:27,038 --> 01:07:28,438
No, thank you.

1310
01:07:29,104 --> 01:07:31,211
Sometimes a father can learn from his son.

1311
01:07:33,330 --> 01:07:36,530
Why don't you just kiss
him and get it over with?

1312
01:07:36,945 --> 01:07:38,185
And you too Joe.

1313
01:07:38,210 --> 01:07:40,763
Get your butt off that
bunk and get in there.

1314
01:07:40,907 --> 01:07:43,043
Alright, the old lady's got a point but

1315
01:07:43,952 --> 01:07:45,938
I don't want anyone kissing me.

1316
01:07:46,185 --> 01:07:48,678
Come on, plant one right here buddy.

1317
01:07:49,018 --> 01:07:50,264
Yeah.

1318
01:07:52,171 --> 01:07:53,171
All right Dooley’s.

1319
01:07:53,375 --> 01:07:55,075
Come on out, you made bail.

1320
01:07:57,315 --> 01:07:58,315
Too bad.

1321
01:07:58,851 --> 01:08:01,515
I was really hoping for a dramatic escape.

1322
01:08:11,432 --> 01:08:13,205
- We made it.
- Thank you brother.

1323
01:08:13,518 --> 01:08:14,518
Thank you.

1324
01:08:16,051 --> 01:08:18,370
I'm gonna take a nice hot shower.

1325
01:08:18,557 --> 01:08:22,371
Look, I just want you all to know I do
expect to be reimbursed for the bail, OK?

1326
01:08:22,803 --> 01:08:26,053
Because trust me, the money I put up we
could have bought our own hot air balloon.

1327
01:08:26,388 --> 01:08:27,536
Well, that's great.

1328
01:08:27,761 --> 01:08:30,221
We're checking out,
I'll get your mother's stuff for you.

1329
01:08:30,845 --> 01:08:33,181
Well, hurry up.
Because we're out of here too.

1330
01:08:36,031 --> 01:08:37,317
What's your hurry?

1331
01:08:37,802 --> 01:08:40,611
Nobody goes anywhere
till I get my birthday cake.

1332
01:08:40,645 --> 01:08:44,305
M is for the many years
you've been on this planet.

1333
01:08:46,225 --> 01:08:48,317
O is for other people

1334
01:08:48,577 --> 01:08:49,577
your age

1335
01:08:50,072 --> 01:08:51,512
who are no longer with us.

